---
import Seo from "../../components/Seo.astro";
import Nav from "../../components/Nav.astro";
import Footer from "../../components/Footer.astro";
import "../../styles/global.css";

const schema = {
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@graph": [
    { "@type": "EducationalOrganization", "@id": "https://credentialstudy.com/#org", name: "CredentialStudy", url: "https://credentialstudy.com/" },
    {
      "@type": "BreadcrumbList",
      itemListElement: [
        { "@type": "ListItem", position: 1, name: "Home", item: "https://credentialstudy.com/" },
        { "@type": "ListItem", position: 2, name: "How it works", item: "https://credentialstudy.com/how-it-works/" }
      ]
    }
  ]
};
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <Seo
      title="How it works | CredentialStudy"
      description="How a CredentialStudy microcredential works: focused online study, transparent assessment, a recognised certificate — and who can help fund it."
      canonicalPath="/how-it-works/"
      ogType="article"
      jsonLd={schema}
    />
  </head>
  <body>
    <Nav />
    <main>
      <section class="hero">
        <div class="hero-inner">
          <span class="eyebrow">How it works</span>
          <h1>Learn one thing well — and prove it.</h1>
          <p>A microcredential is short, recognised study focused on a single concrete skill. Here's what to expect.</p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="white">
        <div class="section-inner narrow">
          <div class="section-head compact-head"><span class="kicker">1 · Learn</span><h2>Focused online study, around your job.</h2></div>
          <p>Each programme targets one in-demand skill and is designed to be taken online, part-time, over weeks rather than years. Clear structure, practical tasks, and outcomes you can apply at work the next week.</p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="ice">
        <div class="section-inner narrow">
          <div class="section-head compact-head"><span class="kicker">2 · Prove</span><h2>Transparent, outcome-based assessment.</h2></div>
          <p>You know up front what you'll be able to do at the end and exactly how it's assessed. Assessment is tied to defined learning outcomes — objective and clear, not a black box.</p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="white">
        <div class="section-inner narrow">
          <div class="section-head compact-head"><span class="kicker">3 · Earn</span><h2>A recognised certificate.</h2></div>
          <p>You earn a microcredential aligned with recognised standards — the EU's <em>European Approach to Micro-credentials</em> and EQF levels — that you can show employers, add to your CV and Europass, and stack toward further study.</p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="ice">
        <div class="section-inner narrow">
          <div class="section-head compact-head"><span class="kicker">Funding</span><h2>You may not pay the full price yourself.</h2></div>
          <p>Often an employer's training budget covers upskilling that helps current work. In Estonia, public support such as Töötukassa can also help eligible learners. We'll make funding options clear for each programme.</p>
          <div class="inline-actions"><a class="btn btn-primary" href="/#notify" data-track-event="cta_click" data-track-label="how_notify">Get notified</a></div>
        </div>
      </section>
    </main>
    <Footer label="How it works" />
  </body>
</html>
